# TrendTrack automation (Youry Intelligence)

## Primary doc (paste for LLMs / agents)

Official full reference (single file):

https://docs.trendtrack.io/docs/llms-full.txt

Use it to verify request bodies, `sortBy` values, TTL/credits, and endpoint differences.

## MCP in Cursor (parent workspace)

Remote MCP endpoint: `https://api.trendtrack.io/v1/mcp`

Configured in **`speel 2.0/.cursor/mcp.json`** and optionally **`ugc-automation/.cursor/mcp.json`** as `trendtrack`. MCP is optional вАФ the app uses **`TRENDTRACK_API_KEY`** + `src/lib/trendtrack.ts`.

### Cursor + TrendTrack OAuth error

If logs show **`redirect_uris must be HTTPS URLs or loopback HTTP URLs`**: Cursor proposes a **`cursor://вА¶`** OAuth redirect; TrendTrack only accepts HTTPS or loopback `http`. That blocks MCP OAuth until Cursor or TrendTrack adjust policy. Disable the MCP server in Cursor settings until then, or ask either vendor about compatibility.

## `sortBy` rules

**`POST /v1/ads/query`** only accepts:

`createdAt`, `longestRunning`, `relevance`, `relevanceScore`, `newest`, `mostDuplicates`, `reach`, `reachDelta1d`, `reachDelta7d`, `reachDelta30d`, `adOrder`.

**`GET .../top-ads`** accepts a different set (`currentRank`, `rankDelta*`, вА¶ per docs).

Map UI selections through **`intelligenceUiSortToAdsQuerySort`** in **`src/lib/trendtrackAdsQuerySort.ts`** before calling `ttQueryAds`. Never send `currentRank` to `/v1/ads/query`.

English UI copy only.
